175:/* 
176:    Memory Bank Selection Logic:
177:
178:    During a write operation the CPU will indicate via the SIZE0-1 and A0-1 pins the number of bytes being written
179:    and the location of the writes on theh 32 bit databus.  It is possible for the CPU to write to a single byte location 
180:    inside of a 32 bit wide memory.  As such we need to have individual control over which part of the data bus is 
181:    participating in a write. 
182:
183:    It is important to note that for cacheable areas of memory (which in our design is all of the SRAM and 
184:    DRAM areas) - All read operations are 32 Bus Access, and all read operations must return all 4 bytes based 
185:    on the address bus.  This is to guarentee the cache always has the correct full 32 value for an addresss.
186:
187:    SEE DATASHEET for TABLE
188:
189:    For 32bit Bus Write Access:
190:            BA32_LL = Active high flag for the LSB 8 bits, located on D31:D24
191:            BA32_LH = Active high flag for the second LSB 8 bits, located on D23:D16
192:            BA32_UL = Active high flag for the lower MSB 8 bits, located on D15:D8
193:            BA32_UH = Active high flag for the upper MSB 8 bits, located on D7:D0
194:
195:    For 16bit Bus  Write Access:
196:            BA16_LL = Active high flag for the LSB 8 bits, located on D31:D24
197:            BA16_LH = Active high flag for the MSB 8 bits, located on D23:D16
198:
199:    For 8bit Bus  Write Access:
200:            BA8 = Active high for all accesses, so hard coded to 1, located on D31:24
201:
202:*/
203:
204:BA32_LL = (!CPU_AA0 & !CPU_AA1);
205:BA32_LH = !((CPU_AA1 # (!CPU_AA0 & CPU_SIZ0 & !CPU_SIZ1)));
206:BA32_UL = !(( (!CPU_AA1 & CPU_SIZ0 & !CPU_SIZ1) 
207:            # (CPU_AA1 & CPU_AA0) 
208:            # (!CPU_AA0 & !CPU_AA1 & !CPU_SIZ0 & CPU_SIZ1)
209:           ));
210:BA32_UH = (   (CPU_AA1 & CPU_SIZ1) 
211:            # (!CPU_SIZ1 & !CPU_SIZ0) 
212:            # (CPU_AA0 & CPU_SIZ1 & CPU_SIZ0) 
213:            # (CPU_AA0 & CPU_AA1)
214:          );
